## 3. RBAC MATRIX

### Current State: `[BROKEN]`

```php
// Only checks JWT validity, NOT role
$authMiddleware = function (Request $request, $handler) use ($jwtSecret) {
    // ... validates token exists and is valid
    // NEVER checks: $decoded->role === 'admin'
}
```

### Required Access Matrix

| Role | /admin/* | /students | /teacher/* | /student/* | /attendance |
|------|----------|-----------|------------|------------|-------------|
| Admin | ✅ C/R/U/D | ✅ All | ✅ All | ✅ All | ✅ All |
| Teacher | ❌ | ✅ Own classes | ✅ Own | ❌ | ✅ Own classes |
| Student | ❌ | ✅ Self only | ❌ | ✅ Own | ✅ View self |
| Employee | ❌ | ❌ | ❌ | ❌ | ❌ |

### JWT Payload (Current)

```json
{
  "user_id": "0000000001",
  "username": "admin",
  "role": "admin",
  "role_name": "Administrator",
  "role_id": "001",
  "exp": 1770503095
}
```

### Required Middleware (TO IMPLEMENT)

```php
// Role-based middleware factory
function requireRole(array $allowedRoles) {
    return function (Request $request, $handler) use ($allowedRoles) {
        $user = $request->getAttribute('user');
        if (!in_array($user->role, $allowedRoles)) {
            $response = new \Slim\Psr7\Response();
            $response->getBody()->write(json_encode([
                'error' => 'Forbidden',
                'message' => 'Insufficient permissions'
            ]));
            return $response->withStatus(403);
        }
        return $handler->handle($request);
    };
}

// Usage on admin routes:
$app->get('/admin/users', ...)->add($authMiddleware)->add(requireRole(['admin']));

// For teacher routes with scope filter:
$app->get('/teacher/students', function($req, $res) {
    $user = $req->getAttribute('user');
    // WHERE class_id IN (SELECT class_id FROM gibbonCourseClassPerson WHERE gibbonPersonID = $user->user_id)
})->add($authMiddleware)->add(requireRole(['admin', 'teacher']));
```

