## 4. API ↔ UI CONTRACT

### Working Endpoints

| Feature | Method | Endpoint | UI Component | Status |
|---------|--------|----------|--------------|--------|
| Login | POST | /auth/login | Login.tsx | ✅ |
| Admin Stats | GET | /admin/stats | AdminDashboard.tsx | ✅ |
| Notices CRUD | GET/POST/PUT/DELETE | /admin/notices | ManageNotices.tsx | ✅ |
| Gallery CRUD | GET/POST/PUT/DELETE | /admin/gallery | ManageGallery.tsx | ✅ |
| Users CRUD | GET/POST/DELETE | /admin/users | ManageUsers.tsx | ✅ |
| Audit Logs | GET | /admin/audit-logs | AuditLogs.tsx | ✅ |
| Contact | POST | /contact | Contact.tsx | ✅ |
| Public Notices | GET | /notices | Notices.tsx | ✅ |
| Public Gallery | GET | /gallery | Gallery.tsx | ✅ |

### Missing Endpoints (MUST BUILD)

| Feature | Method | Endpoint | Request | Response | UI |
|---------|--------|----------|---------|----------|-----|
| Mark Attendance | POST | /attendance/mark | `{student_id, date, code}` | `{success, record_id}` | AttendanceManagement.tsx |
| Get Attendance | GET | /attendance?class_id=X&date=Y | - | `{students: [{id, name, status}]}` | AttendanceManagement.tsx |
| Student Dashboard | GET | /student/dashboard | - | `{profile, attendance, timetable, notifications}` | StudentDashboard.tsx |
| Teacher Classes | GET | /teacher/classes | - | `{classes: [{id, name, students}]}` | TeacherDashboard.tsx |
| Teacher Timetable | GET | /teacher/timetable | - | `{days: [{slots}]}` | TeacherDashboard.tsx |
| Courses List | GET | /courses | - | `{courses: [{id, name, department}]}` | Courses.tsx |
| Course Detail | GET | /courses/{id} | - | `{id, name, description, teachers}` | CourseDetail.tsx |

### Example: Attendance Mark API Contract

```bash
# cURL
curl -X POST http://localhost:8000/attendance/mark \
  -H "Authorization: Bearer $TOKEN" \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{
    "class_id": "001",
    "date": "2026-02-08",
    "records": [
      {"student_id": "0000000002", "code": "present"},
      {"student_id": "0000000003", "code": "absent"}
    ]
  }'
```

```typescript
// TypeScript Response Interface
interface AttendanceMarkResponse {
  success: boolean;
  records_saved: number;
  errors?: string[];
}
```

